ParserGirl is minimal very fast xml/html parser.

It consists of exactly one method, "find" which will take a tag-name like "div"
or "a" as string. "find" returns an array of results. It takes a block and
offers tag content and tag attributes as block parameters.

The search haystack can either be set in the constructor or given with "find" as
second param.


Sample finds are:

p = ParserGirl.new


#without haystack "find" takes the haystack from constructor if given
result_array = p.find("a", haystack) do |tag_content, tag_attributes|
  #tag_content is String
  #tag_attributes is Hash
  if tag_attributes[:href] =~ /imdb\.com/
    #search in tag content for more
    p.find("span", tag_content) do |span_content, span_attr|
      "span contains #{span_content}"
    end #do nothing with the result and return it
  end
end.compact.flatten #throw away nil values and flatten the spans

puts result_array.join("\n")


#calling "find" without block returns an array of tag_contents
result_array = p.find("a", haystack).compact

puts result_array.join("\n")
